  "response": "There are several ways to address bumps on your nose, depending on their cause:\n\n1. Acne bumps:\n- Use salicylic acid or benzoyl peroxide treatments\n- Keep skin clean and moisturized\n- Avoid touching or picking at bumps\n- Use non-comedogenic skincare products\n\n2. Blackheads/whiteheads:\n- Exfoliate regularly\n- Use clay masks\n- Try chemical peels\n- Use pore strips\n\n3. Sebaceous hyperplasia (oil gland bumps):\n- Consult a dermatologist\n- Consider professional treatments like:\n  - Laser therapy\n  - Cryotherapy\n  - Electrocautery\n\n4. Milia (small white bumps):\n- Gentle exfoliation\n- Retinoid creams\n- Professional extraction by a dermatologist\n\n5. Skin texture improvement:\n- Stay hydrated\n- Maintain a healthy diet\n- Use sunscreen\n- Get regular facials\n- Consider professional treatments like microdermabrasion\n\n6. For persistent or concerning bumps:\n- Consult a dermatologist for personalized advice\n- Get professional diagnosis and treatment\n\nAlways patch test new products and introduce them gradually to avoid irritation.",
